        if (120 % i == 0 && 40 % i == 0) {
            count++;
        }
    }
    printf("%d\n", count);
    return 0;
}

The program above counts the number of positive divisors that 120 and 40 have in common. Let's run this program or calculate manually:

The divisors of 120 are: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 10, 12, 15, 20, 24, 30, 40, 60, 120.
The divisors of 40 are: 1, 2, 4, 5, 8, 10, 20, 40.

The common divisors of 120 and 40 are: 1, 2, 4, 5, 8, 10, 20, 40.

So there are 8 common positive divisors.
$\boxed{8}$

